1
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,175
It is not over yet.

2
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:03,813
Now…

3
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:08,318
let us make a pact.

4
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:14,240
I will give you half of my Yang energy.
In exchange…

5
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:18,244
help me.

6
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,256
Damn it.

7
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:50,837
At this rate,

8
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:53,756
your soul will be destroyed.

9
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:58,219
If you reveal your true self now,

10
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:01,806
I will grant you the chance to pass on.

11
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:46,059
No.

12
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:48,686
That is not what we agreed to.

13
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:51,731
If I lose all my Yang energy…

14
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:54,901
I will die.

15
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:19,402
I told you not to pull…

16
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:36,544
THE EAST PALACE

17
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:44,177
Are you all right?

18
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,931
Prince Yeongan is safe.

19
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:52,226
You were the one who saved him,
were you not?

20
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:56,439
More importantly,
why did you pull the rope?

21
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,817
The bell suddenly stopped ringing.

22
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:02,153
I thought you might be in danger,
so I pulled it.

23
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:04,572
Did I interrupt?

24
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:10,411
I clearly told you not to pull that rope,
but you never listen.

25
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,080
Good grief.

26
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:15,833
Did you get rid of the pond spirit?

27
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,129
I merely drained a portion of its power.

28
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:24,050
Even so, it will not be able to move
for a while.

29
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:35,937
Why that look?

30
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:36,979
Well,

31
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:42,693
I regret taking you for nothing
but a layabout and a swindler.

32
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:45,154
I once thought

33
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:49,367
you were a heartless man
who cared little for human lives…

34
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:50,284
Goodness.

35
00:06:51,619 --> 00:06:52,829
…and only for himself.

36
00:06:56,290 --> 00:07:00,002
Well, that is not entirely wrong.
Yet it does not feel so…

37
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:02,547
In any case,

38
00:07:03,714 --> 00:07:06,884
His Majesty will be grateful
that you saved Prince Yeongan.

39
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:11,097
Then would you ask your father
to let me leave the palace?

40
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:18,104
How did you find out?

41
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:22,150
- Since when?
- From the moment I first saw you.

42
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:26,863
I wondered who His Majesty
would send in secret,

43
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:29,282
but a court lady with delicate hands?
Impossible.

44
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,326
Are you all right?

45
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:37,874
- And you look exactly like the King.
- Huh?

46
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,000
The strong presence

47
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:43,129
and that stubborn look.

48
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:47,508
Wait, is that why you told me
to show my blood earlier?

49
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:52,930
You used me as bait, knowing the spirit
held a grudge against the royal bloodline?

50
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:56,350
I needed to distract the pond spirit.

51
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:59,103
At least His Majesty chose
the right person.

52
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:08,988
Speaking of which…

53
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:18,581
How about joining hands with me
in secret from His Majesty?

54
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:24,128
Here.

55
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:35,556
I can only stay here to watch you
while you resolve the pond spirit matter.

56
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,558
So

57
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:41,020
buy me time in the palace.

58
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:44,690
What do you plan to do meanwhile?

59
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:46,943
I am going to kill

60
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:48,778
someone in the palace.

61
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:50,905
<i>Your Majesty.</i>

62
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,492
A child who once served
the late Crown Prince

63
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:57,078
requested an audience with you.

64
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,460
He claims to know something

65
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:07,088
about the Crown Prince
and the pond spirit.

66
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,510
Let him in.

67
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:27,817
Very well.

68
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:29,777
Is there

69
00:09:31,195 --> 00:09:32,989
something you must tell me?

70
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:08,608
You are young

71
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:12,320
yet courageous.

72
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:21,912
Yes, right here.

73
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:54,403
<i>Why should I join hands with you</i>
<i>in secret from His Majesty?</i>

74
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:59,575
Because those who learn secrets
of the palace cannot leave alive.

75
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:04,872
So if I help you,
you will let me leave the palace alive?

76
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:31,065
But how did you hear the bell?

77
00:11:34,443 --> 00:11:37,738
I have abilities like yours.

78
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:14,775
Mother!

79
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:16,277
Are you all right?

80
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:19,363
Is there something inside?

81
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:21,490
Princess.

82
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:24,660
What do you think you are doing here?

83
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:27,663
<i>"The pond spirit."</i>

84
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:31,625
"The serpent's cast skin
killed the dragon's child."

85
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:33,961
Those were the words of the spirit

86
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:36,505
that was once trapped there
when I was a child.

87
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:39,508
The dragon's child means
the son of the King,

88
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:42,970
so the serpent's cast skin
must refer to the pond spirit.

89
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:43,888
What are you--

90
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:46,015
In any case,
looking into the salt storehouse

91
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:48,309
will tell us more about the pond spirit.

92
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,565
- Your reason for returning--
- None of your concern.

93
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:00,821
All you need to do
is look into the pond spirit.

94
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:04,700
So you were cast out of the palace
for hearing spirits.

95
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,244
You are a princess,

96
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,246
yet you have shamanic gifts.

97
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:13,167
What happened as a child
that you are able to hear spirits?

98
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:17,671
How were you raised
to twist the knife with every word?

99
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:22,343
You are overly sensitive about nothing.

100
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:23,469
Nothing?

101
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:30,434
Seeing that you do not know
how to consider others' feelings,

102
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,436
even your friends and family
must hate you.

103
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,147
I have neither friends nor family.
I am an orphan.

104
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,735
And you are hardly one to talk.

105
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,279
Do you have any friends?

106
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:46,534
- Are all royalty born insufferable--
- Enough!

107
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,704
Just check the salt storehouse
so you can catch the pond spirit.

108
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:53,916
Good grief.

109
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:55,876
Oh dear.

110
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:58,003
This pond spirit…

111
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:00,548
Hold on.

112
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:05,261
No…

113
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:15,020
Do not tell me…

114
00:14:15,604 --> 00:14:17,523
- Why are you going there?
- It cannot be.

115
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:19,108
- It cannot be.
- What?

116
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:22,027
- Wait.
- Did you find something there?

117
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:28,909
I was saving it for later.

118
00:14:32,788 --> 00:14:33,831
- So it is here.
- What?

119
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,166
- A gwi-mae.
- A gwi-mae?

120
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,793
Must find out what it really is.

121
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:41,088
- Where did the rice cake…
- Wait.

122
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,007
- Why are you throwing--
- Quiet!

123
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,385
Just be quiet for a moment.

124
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:01,317
This is bad. No!

125
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:03,235
What is there?

126
00:15:05,946 --> 00:15:08,240
- Look--
- We need to get out of here.

127
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:10,451
Let us go.

128
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:13,495
- Hurry!
- Wait.

129
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:15,873
We need to check!

130
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:26,842
You said it was a gwi-mae.
And that it is bound to a place.

131
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:29,887
- We should be fine.
- Hold on!

132
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:35,225
That one is called Ggeomeoksali.

133
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:36,810
It is no ordinary creature.

134
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:39,813
It attaches to the living, not places,
feeding on Yang energy.

135
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:44,234
- Yang energy?
- Those drained of it see terror and die.

136
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:47,488
It is a terrifying creature.

137
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:48,530
But…

138
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:51,784
I get it. Stop pushing me.

139
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:52,826
Then

140
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,788
let us go see your new quarters.

141
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:58,958
His Majesty reassigned them
for saving Prince Yeongan.

142
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,919
Why are you telling me this now?

143
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:05,130
- Well…
- Where is it?

144
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:09,134
That way. Over there.

145
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:12,137
Hurry. Quick!

146
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:14,223
I will walk myself.

147
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:18,894
Good grief.

148
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:21,772
I cannot believe this.

149
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:25,776
- Oh dear.
- What are you staring at?

150
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:27,361
I should not have trusted.

151
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:29,196
Good grief. Truly…

152
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,657
How do you like the room?

153
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:38,288
I just moved to the room across.

154
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,124
Goodness.

155
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:45,963
It followed us here.

156
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:48,882
What?

157
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:51,552
Ggeomeoksali.

158
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:52,594
What?

159
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,264
Ggeomeoksali.

160
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,020
No!

161
00:17:02,604 --> 00:17:04,648
Goodness. It clings like a leech.

162
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:09,028
What is it now?

163
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:13,949
There is nothing.

164
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:23,375
More importantly,

165
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:28,005
His Majesty seems pleased
about the Prince Yeongan matter.

166
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,049
That is a relief.

167
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:31,759
Relief? Hardly.

168
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:34,678
If the pond spirit appears again,

169
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:37,806
Prince Yeongan will surely die.

170
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:46,023
Please get through this.

171
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:48,859
Give it to me.

172
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:52,821
Please come to your senses.

173
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:06,919
Your Majesty, Prince Yeongan,
the last remaining, lies so ill.

174
00:18:07,002 --> 00:18:10,047
I truly fear for the royal succession.

175
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,674
Uncanny, ceaseless calamities
in the East Palace

176
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:15,969
are shaking the very foundation
of this nation.

177
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:19,223
The foundations of the nation are shaken?

178
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:21,475
Watch your tongues.

179
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:23,435
So long as I draw breath,

180
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:27,439
the foundations of this nation
will not be shaken.

181
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:31,819
Your Majesty, Prince Iksang has arrived.

182
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:37,574
- Why is Prince Iksang…
- Greetings.

183
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,827
Have you had your meal?

184
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:45,165
You look even younger, Aunt.

185
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:50,087
You still address me that way,
Prince Iksang.

186
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:53,340
So, how have you been?

187
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:56,176
I went on a tiger hunt in Hobyeong Valley.

188
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:59,138
I enjoyed some leisure
in Hwayang Valley as well.

189
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:03,809
Your Majesty, you should not stay
confined to the palace.

190
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:07,062
Some rest beyond its walls
would serve you well.

191
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:09,273
I am not sure.

192
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:12,734
I entered here as Crown Princess
at the age of 11

193
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:15,612
and have never set foot beyond the walls.

194
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:20,409
This palace is where I am to remain
until the day I die.

195
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:23,871
You remain unchanged.

196
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:26,123
But why did you wish to see me?

197
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,088
How is your son doing?

198
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:44,683
He is doing well.

199
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:50,314
Unlike me,
he delights in scholarly pursuits.

200
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:55,485
After all, royal relatives are barred
from holding office.

201
00:19:56,236 --> 00:20:01,783
A small stream cannot travel far
once it leaves the main flow.

202
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:07,372
But if the main river
turns foul and runs dry…

203
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:14,588
we should cut it off
and open a new channel, should we not?

204
00:20:15,964 --> 00:20:17,716
<i>How dare a mere feng shui master</i>

205
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:20,761
seek an audience
with Her Majesty so easily.

206
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:22,387
Leave at once.

207
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:25,599
He entered the palace
on His Majesty's command.

208
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:28,060
He has something to report to Her Majesty.

209
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,188
It is also the will of His Majesty.

210
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:34,149
Wait here.

211
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:44,326
She is damn prickly.

212
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:49,164
She is the highest elder
of the Internal Court.

213
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,875
Do you think an audience
is easily granted?

214
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:01,885
I hear a strange noise.

215
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:21,154
This damn Yin energy in the palace…

216
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:40,924
Her Majesty is occupied.

217
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:42,509
You may withdraw.

218
00:21:46,263 --> 00:21:48,515
Goodness, what a shame.

219
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:51,685
I had something to report
about the pond spirit.

220
00:21:51,768 --> 00:21:54,438
What did you say? The pond spirit?

221
00:21:56,815 --> 00:21:58,859
Then please deliver this message.

222
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:04,031
Once Prince Yeongan is dead,

223
00:22:04,531 --> 00:22:07,409
Her Majesty should consider
who comes next.

224
00:22:08,368 --> 00:22:09,328
What?

225
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:10,704
Next?

226
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:17,961
What do you…

227
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,845
This was a wasted trip.

228
00:22:28,805 --> 00:22:32,100
- Meeting the Queen Dowager at all--
- No, there is a gain.

229
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:34,186
A gain? What do you mean?

230
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,147
Wait. You are…

231
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:48,700
She lives in a private residence.

232
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:51,036
Why is she here in the palace?

233
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:56,625
Who is that? Do you know each other?

234
00:22:57,125 --> 00:23:01,338
She is my grandmother
and the birth mother of His Majesty.

235
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:09,805
Is that why the Queen Dowager
and the King are at odds?

236
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,765
Because they are not related by blood?

237
00:23:13,934 --> 00:23:18,438
More likely, His Majesty was born
to a court lady who became a concubine.

238
00:23:21,691 --> 00:23:23,193
<i>Thirty years ago,</i>

239
00:23:24,194 --> 00:23:29,157
<i>all of my father's brothers died</i>
<i>for unknown reasons.</i>

240
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:34,538
<i>He was the only surviving son</i>
<i>of the late King and became Crown Prince,</i>

241
00:23:35,038 --> 00:23:37,749
<i>but Her Majesty did not recognize him</i>

242
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:40,377
<i>due to the lowborn blood in his veins.</i>

243
00:23:42,462 --> 00:23:45,132
<i>Even now, after he became King.</i>

244
00:23:57,769 --> 00:23:58,728
Your Majesty.

245
00:23:59,229 --> 00:24:03,650
For the nation and its people,
you must appoint a new Crown Prince.

246
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:05,735
I am aware of this.

247
00:24:06,236 --> 00:24:10,323
But Prince Yeongan has yet to recover.

248
00:24:10,407 --> 00:24:12,826
That is precisely why we say this.

249
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:16,037
Your Majesty, measures must be taken.

250
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:18,874
What measures?

251
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:25,255
You must select one of the royal kin
and name him Crown Prince.

252
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:28,091
Please grant your approval.

253
00:24:28,592 --> 00:24:31,720
- Please grant your approval.
- Please grant your approval.

254
00:24:34,055 --> 00:24:37,309
Are you of the belief

255
00:24:39,102 --> 00:24:40,520
that my son will die?

256
00:24:42,022 --> 00:24:44,441
How could we harbor
such irreverent thoughts…

257
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:47,152
That is not what we intend.

258
00:24:47,235 --> 00:24:48,528
You did not intend it?!

259
00:24:50,363 --> 00:24:51,907
Then whose intention is it?

260
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:57,829
The Queen Dowager?

261
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:04,211
I am deeply disappointed in you.

262
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:07,839
I went to great lengths
to bring you into the palace,

263
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:12,302
yet you failed to control even one spirit
and instead cured Prince Yeongan.

264
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:15,931
I did not drive the spirit out.

265
00:25:16,973 --> 00:25:20,060
I meant to draw it to Prince Yeongan.

266
00:25:20,143 --> 00:25:22,771
Then was there someone who drove it out?

267
00:25:23,271 --> 00:25:25,982
The feng shui master the King brought in
seems suspicious.

268
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:28,860
What? The feng shui master
the King brought in?

269
00:25:37,577 --> 00:25:40,038
Keep a close eye on him.

270
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,500
If he truly has the power
to get rid of spirits…

271
00:25:46,086 --> 00:25:47,546
we must kill him.

272
00:25:48,922 --> 00:25:52,300
As the spirits run rampant in the palace,
the King is driven into a corner,

273
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:54,511
and that serves me well.

274
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:58,598
Prince Iksang was
at the Queen Dowager's residence?

275
00:26:02,727 --> 00:26:05,397
Truly impressive.

276
00:26:13,989 --> 00:26:18,076
So she intends to change
the royal bloodline?

277
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:23,832
<i>She means to break the curse</i>
<i>that began 30 years ago</i>

278
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:27,168
<i>and start anew.</i>

279
00:26:28,795 --> 00:26:30,964
<i>Yet it will not be easy.</i>

280
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:37,637
<i>And bound by sin,</i>

281
00:26:38,138 --> 00:26:41,349
<i>how could she flee on her own?</i>

282
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:14,799
Look here.

283
00:27:16,384 --> 00:27:17,302
Look!

284
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:19,095
Wait. What is wrong with you?

285
00:27:24,184 --> 00:27:25,852
Who are you again?

286
00:27:25,935 --> 00:27:27,937
I am Ji-yul,
an apprentice from Saenggwabang.

287
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:31,066
Starting today, I will be sharing
this chamber with you.

288
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:32,901
What? That cannot be.

289
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:33,902
There we go.

290
00:27:34,527 --> 00:27:35,362
Look.

291
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:38,823
I was told I would have my own chamber.

292
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,368
I have never shared one
with anyone before.

293
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:43,495
This must be uncomfortable for you.

294
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:44,996
Not at all.

295
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,956
Before I came to the palace,

296
00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:49,834
my family of nine shared a room.

297
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:52,587
I see.

298
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:57,676
The spirit…

299
00:27:58,843 --> 00:28:01,096
Why is it so noisy out there?

300
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:03,973
What? Oh my! Have you not heard?

301
00:28:04,057 --> 00:28:06,685
A spirit appeared
in the Queen Dowager's residence.

302
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:08,436
- The Queen Dowager's residence?
- Yes.

303
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,606
Ever since I came to the palace,
the spirit incidents keep happening.

304
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:14,275
- It appeared in Saenggwabang as well--
- Wait.

305
00:28:15,068 --> 00:28:17,529
More about the spirit
in the Queen Dowager's residence.

306
00:28:18,488 --> 00:28:20,323
Good grief, it is cold.

307
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,050
Damn it.

308
00:28:41,177 --> 00:28:42,011
What the…

309
00:28:42,595 --> 00:28:44,055
When did you get in here?

310
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:47,642
Stop.

311
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:50,061
You.

312
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,480
Who said you could act cute?

313
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:56,234
Why me of all people? Why?

314
00:28:56,317 --> 00:28:57,986
Why? Damn it…

315
00:28:59,487 --> 00:29:02,323
The salt storehouse spirit is
in the Queen Dowager's residence.

316
00:29:03,616 --> 00:29:05,285
- The Queen Dowager?
- Let us go.

317
00:29:05,368 --> 00:29:07,162
We must look into the salt storehouse.

318
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:10,373
Very well.
I want to get out of here as well.

319
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:12,167
What?

320
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:36,649
Can you hear anything?

321
00:29:38,568 --> 00:29:39,903
What are they saying?

322
00:29:41,237 --> 00:29:44,324
I cannot make out what they are saying.
Their voices are too low.

323
00:29:51,414 --> 00:29:52,999
I need to go inside.

324
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:06,095
Must you go in alone?

325
00:30:11,351 --> 00:30:12,477
I will be fine.

326
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:15,230
Then I will wait here.

327
00:31:11,327 --> 00:31:12,662
Tell me.

328
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:15,582
What do you wish to say?

329
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:23,131
Please clear our names.

330
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,384
So unjust…

331
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:43,610
The serpent's cast skin

332
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,696
killed the dragon's child.

333
00:31:47,196 --> 00:31:51,117
<i>"The serpent's cast skin</i>
<i>killed the dragon's child."</i>

334
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:54,078
Tell me who wrote these words.

335
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:59,167
The dragon's child
refers to the late Crown Prince.

336
00:31:59,834 --> 00:32:02,503
Her Majesty the Queen
was born in the Year of the Snake.

337
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:07,467
This means the Crown Prince died
because of Her Majesty.

338
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:12,263
One of you must have defiled
the royal house.

339
00:32:14,265 --> 00:32:16,559
You will be confined and starved
until you confess.

340
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:18,853
You will not be given a drop of water!

341
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:43,544
Please save us!

342
00:32:46,589 --> 00:32:48,591
Please save us!

343
00:32:50,593 --> 00:32:51,844
Please!

344
00:33:01,688 --> 00:33:03,564
They were burned to death?

345
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:10,613
Place the bones of the dead court ladies
in jars and bury them.

346
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:14,993
Their resentment must be sealed
so it cannot harm the royal house.

347
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:15,994
Yes, Your Majesty.

348
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:39,976
Have you looked into
who broke the sealed jars?

349
00:33:40,977 --> 00:33:42,437
I looked into it

350
00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:46,274
but could not find anyone
who entered the salt storehouse.

351
00:33:48,776 --> 00:33:51,112
This must have been done

352
00:33:51,654 --> 00:33:53,948
by someone who knows
exactly what the jars contain.

353
00:33:55,074 --> 00:33:58,494
But we alone know of those jars.

354
00:33:59,787 --> 00:34:02,206
This must be aimed at me.

355
00:34:02,290 --> 00:34:03,458
Who could it be…

356
00:34:06,794 --> 00:34:07,795
Yes.

357
00:34:08,921 --> 00:34:11,007
There is one more person.

358
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:13,092
Who is it?

359
00:34:14,510 --> 00:34:18,639
I must have been blinded
by fear of the spirit for a moment.

360
00:34:18,723 --> 00:34:20,975
Why did I not see it sooner?

361
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:24,729
<i>The trouble began</i>
<i>after I met Prince Iksang.</i>

362
00:34:24,812 --> 00:34:26,939
He has pulled through.

363
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:31,569
I believe it is time
to appoint a Crown Prince.

364
00:34:31,652 --> 00:34:34,906
<i>His Majesty saw right through me!</i>

365
00:34:35,448 --> 00:34:37,700
He is trying to stop me.

366
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:40,411
He means to use the spirit against me.

367
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:43,706
His Majesty wants me to die tonight!

368
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,379
<i>But I will not allow that to happen.</i>

369
00:34:50,463 --> 00:34:53,424
<i>I will not die to a mere spirit.</i>

370
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:55,968
Night will soon fall.

371
00:34:56,052 --> 00:34:57,970
Court ladies, do not sleep.

372
00:34:58,054 --> 00:35:01,265
Protect me from the spirit!

373
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:03,476
<i>So,</i>

374
00:35:03,559 --> 00:35:04,894
for 30 years,

375
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:08,356
the pond spirit has been killing
the princes of the East Palace,

376
00:35:09,148 --> 00:35:13,736
and the court ladies claimed the princes
were dying because of the Queen Dowager?

377
00:35:14,237 --> 00:35:18,074
It was not the court ladies.
They were falsely accused and killed.

378
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:22,995
What is certain is that the Queen Dowager
is connected to the pond spirit.

379
00:35:25,039 --> 00:35:26,541
Yet, thanks to your ability,

380
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:29,252
I now understand why the court ladies
became won-gwi.

381
00:35:30,545 --> 00:35:32,463
I could not have done it alone.

382
00:35:33,631 --> 00:35:34,757
You did well.

383
00:35:37,343 --> 00:35:38,553
You are the first

384
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:42,014
to find this strange ability useful.

385
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:43,516
Is that so?

386
00:35:43,599 --> 00:35:47,103
I thought His Majesty sent you to me
because he valued your ability.

387
00:35:47,186 --> 00:35:50,189
I suppose I was of some use
in dealing with spirits.

388
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:56,946
You on bad terms with your father?

389
00:36:01,701 --> 00:36:03,369
Hold your tongue.

390
00:36:03,452 --> 00:36:09,208
Do not say
that my own child hears such things.

391
00:36:09,750 --> 00:36:12,295
Unless you mean to disgrace
the royal house.

392
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:18,968
One born of the royal blood who hears
strange things would be a disgrace.

393
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:24,015
Good.

394
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:28,686
What do you mean?

395
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:31,189
I mean,

396
00:36:32,064 --> 00:36:33,774
since we both dislike His Majesty,

397
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:36,027
it suddenly feels like
we are on the same side.

398
00:36:38,654 --> 00:36:40,323
More importantly,

399
00:36:41,949 --> 00:36:44,702
when I heard the cries
from the salt storehouse back then,

400
00:36:45,203 --> 00:36:46,454
I should have helped.

401
00:36:48,122 --> 00:36:50,666
If only I had broken the jars
that held their souls…

402
00:36:51,167 --> 00:36:53,628
What could a mere child have done?

403
00:36:54,128 --> 00:36:56,714
It must have been hard
to bear that strange gift.

404
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,592
Do not blame yourself.

405
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:09,560
I, too, was feared and pointed at.

406
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:13,022
You can simply ignore such people.

407
00:37:16,859 --> 00:37:19,820
Just beware of the spirits

408
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:22,156
so you do not end up getting possessed.

409
00:37:29,497 --> 00:37:30,539
Now I understand

410
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:32,792
why you are so peculiar.

411
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:34,418
Me?

412
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,964
I will lay the bones to rest.

413
00:37:38,047 --> 00:37:40,007
Look. Hold on.

414
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:43,177
What? I will have these bones
of the court ladies ground to powder.

415
00:37:43,678 --> 00:37:44,679
What?

416
00:37:46,180 --> 00:37:47,640
Ground to powder?

417
00:37:48,808 --> 00:37:50,142
No, you must not!

418
00:37:51,143 --> 00:37:54,480
- Do you mean to dishonor the dead again?
- Good grief.

419
00:37:54,981 --> 00:37:57,024
I am tired of explaining it every time.

420
00:37:57,525 --> 00:38:01,028
Won-gwi is a spirit that cannot pass on

421
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:03,155
because it carries resentment.

422
00:38:03,781 --> 00:38:06,784
So if you use things
that remind it of who it once was

423
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:08,744
and dissolve that mass of resentment…

424
00:38:10,830 --> 00:38:12,498
you may send it to the afterlife.

425
00:38:13,207 --> 00:38:16,043
Then those souls will not disappear,
will they?

426
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:17,295
They are pitiful souls.

427
00:38:17,378 --> 00:38:19,672
Pitiful or not,

428
00:38:19,755 --> 00:38:22,800
they are harming innocent people.

429
00:38:23,426 --> 00:38:25,594
- We have no time.
- What do you mean?

430
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:28,097
Are you telling me
that spirits will appear again?

431
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:33,894
It must be right
by the Queen Dowager already.

432
00:39:01,130 --> 00:39:03,049
Is there no one outside?

433
00:39:04,050 --> 00:39:06,218
Bring me a candle.

434
00:39:31,410 --> 00:39:36,415
<i>You should take these ashes to the shrine</i>
<i>where the Queen Dowager is.</i>

435
00:39:37,917 --> 00:39:42,171
<i>I will go into the Realm of Gwi</i>
<i>and seek the spirits out.</i>

436
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:46,926
<i>They should be right beside</i>
<i>the Queen Dowager.</i>

437
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:16,038
I am sorry.

438
00:40:47,486 --> 00:40:50,531
<i>As you said, they are innocent won-gwi.</i>

439
00:40:53,325 --> 00:40:56,245
<i>To release their grudge,</i>
<i>we must destroy that mass of resentment.</i>

440
00:40:58,831 --> 00:41:02,042
<i>Begin when I ring the bell.</i>

441
00:42:57,533 --> 00:42:59,743
<i>Is this the only way?</i>

442
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:05,791
At this rate, I will be the one to die.

443
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:34,695
Hurry!

444
00:43:35,195 --> 00:43:36,614
Quick!

445
00:44:14,610 --> 00:44:16,111
<i>Let go of your grievances…</i>

446
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:20,741
<i>release your anger</i>…

447
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:26,288
<i>and rest in peace.</i>

448
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:32,586
<i>I will send you to the afterlife.</i>

449
00:44:34,129 --> 00:44:35,631
<i>May you all</i>…

450
00:44:38,425 --> 00:44:41,178
<i>be reborn in paradise.</i>

451
00:45:11,458 --> 00:45:14,795
We were wronged.

452
00:45:14,878 --> 00:45:17,715
This is unjust.

453
00:45:19,591 --> 00:45:22,428
We were wronged.

454
00:45:23,929 --> 00:45:26,056
This is unjust.

455
00:45:26,765 --> 00:45:30,102
- What you did to my mother and me…
- We were wronged.

456
00:45:30,185 --> 00:45:31,812
I have not forgotten at all.

457
00:45:32,312 --> 00:45:37,484
This is most… unjust.

458
00:45:37,985 --> 00:45:40,446
What is it that you find unjust?

459
00:45:46,410 --> 00:45:47,953
Our only sin

460
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:52,750
was being there.

461
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:54,084
Who…

462
00:45:55,127 --> 00:45:56,628
Who are you?

463
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:04,344
When the Most Favored Lady of the Court
uttered a curse as she died…

464
00:46:09,933 --> 00:46:14,480
No royal blood shall flow
in this palace any longer.

465
00:46:14,563 --> 00:46:17,357
You insolent wench, how dare you!

466
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:20,068
I will die, become a spirit,

467
00:46:20,694 --> 00:46:23,530
and sever the royal bloodline.

468
00:46:24,239 --> 00:46:26,325
I will eradicate the royal bloodline

469
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:29,953
and wipe out every last seed
of the East Palace!

470
00:46:31,205 --> 00:46:32,456
What are you waiting for?

471
00:46:43,258 --> 00:46:46,970
<i>"No royal blood shall flow</i>
<i>in this palace any longer."</i>

472
00:46:48,013 --> 00:46:50,516
<i>"I will wipe out every last seed</i>
<i>of the East Palace."</i>

473
00:46:51,016 --> 00:46:55,562
<i>She killed us for hearing the curse</i>
<i>of the Most Favored Lady of the Court.</i>

474
00:46:57,648 --> 00:47:00,984
<i>"The serpent's cast skin</i>
<i>killed the dragon's child."</i>

475
00:47:02,110 --> 00:47:06,490
<i>Using the writing on the wall</i>
<i>as an excuse!</i>

476
00:47:12,162 --> 00:47:13,789
The Most Favored Lady of the Court?

477
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:22,130
Then the pond spirit is
the Most Favored Lady of the Court?

478
00:47:24,174 --> 00:47:27,803
We were wronged.

479
00:47:29,847 --> 00:47:32,766
While we were dying,

480
00:47:33,559 --> 00:47:37,896
why did you just stand by?

481
00:47:39,398 --> 00:47:43,777
<i>Those who sin are punished eventually.</i>

482
00:47:47,114 --> 00:47:49,616
<i>You need not take a life.</i>

483
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:53,759
Subtitle translation by: Yun-hee Jang
